It is shaping up to be a cold weekend, with low temperatures and rainfall expected in some parts of the country.  The Kenya Meteorological Department (MET) on Friday said that rain is expected in parts of Nairobi County over the next 24 hours.  Areas of Roysambu, Ruaraka, Embakasi South, Embakasi West, Embakasi Central and Kamukunji are “likely to be cold and cloudy with rainfall”.  Some parts of Rift Valley, Western, Nyanza, Central and Eastern regions will not be sapred either, with bouts of rain expected. Help us serve you better by completing our quick survey. “Rains are expected over several parts of Narok, Nyamira, Nakuru, Kericho, Nandi, Homabay, Nyeri, Kakamega, Vihiga, Busia, Bungoma, Kisumu, Kisii, Siaya, Bomet, Elgeyo Marakwet, Baringo, Uasin Gishu, trans Nzoia, Muranga, Kirinyaga, Embu, Meru and Kiambu,” the weatherman said.  Linking SGR to old railway will spur economic growth of the region  8,667 to benefit from Sh60 million medical cover in Bomet  Three-star general tactfully changing face of the capital  Olympics: Selemon Barega of Ethiopia extends Kenya's 53 years wait after winning 10,000m On August 10, MET also warned of overcast weather with storm and rain expected over the Highlands West of the Rift valley, the Lake Victoria basin, the South and Central Rift Valley, Northwest and Highlands east of the Rift Valley.  However, counties in the Northeast are likely to experience sunny and dry conditions, and strong winds to prevail in parts of Coast in the next four days.    Government sets aside Ksh 7 billion for vaccines to acquire two different types of Covid-19 vaccines  Watoto watatu wa familia moja wafukiwa na ardhi kwenye kisima Bomet   Isaac Ruto joins CORD in push for the disbandment of IEBC By Betty Njeru | 2 hours ago By Roselyne Obala | 5 hours ago By Ndungu Gachane | 5 hours ago By Brian Okoth | 5 hours ago